## Why This Is Asked
This question tests practical knowledge of implementing isolated tenant onboarding in HashiCorp Vault Enterprise using the Transit secrets engine. It validates understanding of per-tenant boundaries, authentication with AppRole, short-lived tokens with TTL, and proper rollback procedures.

## Key Concepts
- **Transit Mounting Per Tenant**: Isolates encryption keys per tenant namespace using dedicated mount paths
- **Per-Tenant Policy and AppRole**: Implements least-privilege access control with time-bound credentials
- **Short-Lived Tokens and Lease Revocation**: Ensures tokens automatically expire and can be explicitly revoked for security
- **Audit Verification**: Confirms tenant isolation and provides compliance evidence of cleanup

## Code Example
```javascript
// Sample Node.js client workflow
const vault = require('node-vault')({ endpoint: 'https://vault.enterprise.com' });

async function tenantWorkflow() {
  // Login via AppRole
  const login = await vault.approle.login({
    role_id: 'role-id-from-vault',
    secret_id: 'secret-id-from-vault'
  });
  vault.token = login.auth.client_token;

  // Encrypt
  const encrypt = await vault.transit.encrypt(
    'tenant-<id>/tenant-<id>-enc',
    { plaintext: Buffer.from('sensitive-data').toString('base64') }
  );

  // Decrypt
  const decrypt = await vault.transit.decrypt(
    'tenant-<id>/tenant-<id>-enc',
    { ciphertext: encrypt.data.ciphertext }
  );

  console.log(Buffer.from(decrypt.data.plaintext, 'base64').toString());
}
```

